<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-23T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-23T10:00:00-05:00" n="1046" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1046">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1123 Winterle/3: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-23T11:00:00-04:00">September 23, 1935—11
                                    a.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>3. Your 7, September 21, noon, and Chefoo’s September 21, 4 p.m., to you.
                            Department wondering why Chefoo has not lodged and you have not
                            recommended lodging charge against Japanese policeman. Please inform
                            Department immediately.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>